method: Canopy N% was estimated with the Carnegie Airborne Observatory Airborne Taxonomic Mapping System (CAO-AToMs) onboard a Dornier 228 Aircraft. method: Leaf fracture toughness was measured with a pair of scissors (Dovo, Germany) to control and direct crack growth (Lucas & Pereira 1990). The scissors, with an included angle of 55Â° and a radius of curvature (sharpness) of 1.6 Âµm, were mounted on a portable universal testing machine (Darvell et al. 1996). We fractured leaves in a transverse cut perpendicular to the midrib. This method, described by Lucas et al.
